Notes: The 'row_id' serves as a unique identifier for each problem condition, making 'hasIdentifier' the most appropriate property for mapping.
The 'patient_id' corresponds to the patient linked to the problem condition; 'hasPatient' clearly models this relationship.
The diagnosis_code aligns with coding systems represented by 'Code', making this property appropriate.
The 'created_at' timestamp naturally maps to the 'hasDateTime' property with datatype dateTime.
The 'org_code' specifies the organizational provider, fitting well with 'hasDataProviderInstitute'.
The 'org_name' is a descriptive label, best mapped to 'hasName'.
